The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 October is 4,519 (523 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 October, there were 385 new confirmed cases (44.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 October, there were 383 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 1% ( 2 extra cases).
